1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
AI agents ship to production faster than any prior software category —

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
but the testing discipline traditional software earned over decades hasn't caught up.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:18,000
This is AgentClinic. Every finding bound to evidence in the trace, published natively into UiPath Test Cloud.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Seven deterministic detectors, source-controlled. Every finding must point at specific trace events as evidence —

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:35,000
a finding without an evidence span is a contract violation, rejected at the schema layer.

6
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:43,000
The score is reproducible: same trace, same rules, same number, every time.

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Run it locally first. The CLI normalizes the trace, detects seven waste patterns,

8
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:55,000
scores L0 to L3, then publishes natively into Test Cloud.

9
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:05,000
No mocks. The execution ID, test set, and case log are all real. Live.

10
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Same agent, this time triggered from Automation Cloud.

11
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Same pipeline as the local runtime — but now writing directly into Test Manager.

12
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
One Test Case per pattern, reusable across runs.

13
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:35,000
The evidence-bound reason is visible right in the dialog reviewers already use.

14
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Quality is no longer a late-stage checkpoint.

15
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Four roles, no overlap. Judge is deterministic — the LLM cannot revise the verdict.

16
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Coach rides UiPath's AgentHub LLM Gateway, every call inside the AI Trust Layer.

17
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:01,000
No direct LLM provider API key.

18
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Test Cloud is the system of record. UiPath ties it all together.

19
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Every line of source, every commit message, every documentation file in this repository

20
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:18,000
was written by Claude Code over eleven days.

21
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Twenty-plus commits, every one visible in the log.

22
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:30,000
The human role was driver — framing, vetting, correcting, performing the GUI actions Claude can't.

23
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Repository public, MIT licensed, CI green, error matrix documented.

24
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Drop a trace in, get an audit trail.

25
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:45,000
AgentClinic — coach, not surveillance. Thank you.
